"middle": "Italy's top-tier league has achieved a record market value, with notable gains for Inter Milan and SSC Napoli. Napoli's value has surpassed €640 million for the first time since pre-Coronavirus times, while Inter Milan follows closely behind with an increase of around €22 million. Mike Maignan and Victor Osimhen have seen significant increases in their values, while Sergej Milinkovic-Savic and Milan Skriniar have experienced a drop in value due to their advancing age and lack of market activity. Federico Chiesa has also suffered a decrease in value after a disappointing season marred by injuries.",
"long": "Serie A has set a new record for market value, with a significant jump in squad values for Inter Milan and SSC Napoli. Napoli has broken the €640 million mark for the first time since pre-Coronavirus times, with an additional €11.5 million in revenue. Inter Milan follows closely behind, with an increase of around €22 million, putting them ahead of AC Milan in the Serie A squad value rankings. Mike Maignan and Victor Osimhen have seen their values soar, with Maignan now valued at €45 million and Osimhen at a staggering €120 million, the highest value ever recorded in Serie A history. However, Sergej Milinkovic-Savic and Milan Skriniar have experienced a drop in value due to their advancing age and lack of market activity, with their values now standing at €50 million. Federico Chiesa has also suffered a decrease in value after a forgettable season marred by injuries, with his value now at €40 million. On the German front, Robin Gosens has seen a further decrease in value, now valued at €15 million, as he struggles to secure a starting spot over rival Federico Dimarco. This may lead to his sale to bring fresh financial resources to Inter."}

