"middle": "In the Europa League, four teams have made it to the Round of 16. Atalanta BC dominated hosts Olympiakos Piraeus with a 3-0 victory, following their 2-1 win in the first leg. Ruslan Malinovskyi, who scored twice in the match, used his goal celebration to protest the Russian invasion of his home country, Ukraine. Danish national player Joakim Maehle also scored for Atalanta. Despite their 1-0 loss to Dinamo Zagreb, FC Sevilla advanced thanks to their first leg 3-1 win. Former Dortmund and Bremen player Thomas Delaney was shown a red card in the closing moments of the match. FC Porto managed a 2-2 draw against Lazio Rom, advancing due to their 2-1 win in the first leg. Ciro Immobile put the Italians in the lead, but goals from Mehdi Taremi and Mateus Uribe turned the game in favor of the Champions League dropouts. Danilo Cataldi managed to equalize for Lazio in the 94th minute.",
"long": "In the Europa League, four teams have made it to the Round of 16 after an exciting set of matches. RB Leipzig, Atalanta BC, FC Porto, and FC Sevilla have all advanced to the next round. Atalanta easily overcame hosts Olympiakos Piraeus with a 3-0 win, following their 2-1 victory in the first leg. Ruslan Malinovskyi, who scored twice in the match, used his goal celebration to protest the Russian invasion of his home country, Ukraine. Danish national player Joakim Maehle also scored for Atalanta. Despite their 1-0 loss to Dinamo Zagreb, FC Sevilla advanced thanks to their first leg 3-1 win. Former Dortmund and Bremen player Thomas Delaney was shown a red card in the closing moments of the match. FC Porto managed a 2-2 draw against Lazio Rom, advancing due to their 2-1 win in the first leg. Ciro Immobile put the Italians in the lead, but goals from Mehdi Taremi and Mateus Uribe turned the game in favor of the Champions League dropouts. Danilo Cataldi managed to equalize for Lazio in the 94th minute. These teams have proven their strength and determination in the competition, and fans are eagerly anticipating the next round of matches."}

